# Cloudflare Pages redirect rules.
#
# Format: <from> <to> <status>
# See https://developers.cloudflare.com/pages/configuration/redirects/
#
# ─── 2026-05-18: glossary → termbase URL migration ────────────────
# The Workbench help pages moved from /workbench/glossaries/* and
# /workbench/superlookup/glossary-search/ to /workbench/termbases/*
# and /workbench/superlookup/termbase-search/ for terminology
# consistency (the Workbench UI calls them termbases throughout,
# and v1.10.62+ uses that term in every dialog and tooltip).
#
# 301 redirects so:
#   - External backlinks to the old URLs (anywhere on the web)
#     don't 404
#   - In-app help links from older installed Workbench versions
#     (modules/help_system.py's HelpTopics enum had the old paths
#     baked in; updated in v1.10.76 but already-installed copies
#     still ship the old strings) still land on the right page
#   - Trados plugin v4.19.114 and earlier had no cross-product
#     links to these specific Workbench help pages, but defensive
#     here anyway
#
# Splat redirect covers all six files in the renamed folder in one
# rule; explicit rule for the renamed file in superlookup/.

/workbench/glossaries/*                  /workbench/termbases/:splat              301
/workbench/superlookup/glossary-search/  /workbench/superlookup/termbase-search/  301
